er</i> former Fox Sports executive Patrick Crakes did not send the original=
 email signed by =E2=80=9CA former Fox Sports executive.=E2=80=9D]<br/><br/=
><i>On cord-cutting</i>: =E2=80=9CLast year, I got rid of Comcast after 20-=
plus years, and through multiple moves, to go with YouTube TV.  There were =
two big issues that Comcast never dealt with: 1. Even when they were losing=
 subs, the price never went down, it only kept going up. Plus, Comcast char=
ges for everything: monthly fees for the cable box and an extra box; a mode=
m.<br/>2. Customer service was terrible. I paused YouTube TV over the summe=
r on the computer. I did the same thing with Comcast, and it took multiple =
45-plus-minute calls to get it right. I=E2=80=99d talk to multiple people e=
very time, and I rarely got my problem fixed on the first call. Comcast did=
 always offer more products for me to buy, though.
=E2=80=94<i>A Varsity subscriber</i><br/></td>
